[2026-02-16T23:48:36.398Z] 
========== WORKER QUESTION #1 ==========
[2026-02-16T23:48:36.398Z] What type of multiplayer experience do you want?
Options:
  - Co-op (Recommended): All players work together to complete levels. Shared coin collection, everyone needs to reach the exit. Uses the existing PeerJS P2P foundation.
  - Competitive (Race): Players race to collect coins and reach the exit first. Individual scoring and rankings.
  - Both co-op and competitive: Support both modes — co-op campaign plus a competitive race mode players can choose between.

What's the priority for the first implementation?
Options:
  - Core multiplayer (Recommended): Lobby system (create/join room), rendering remote players, position sync, and basic shared gameplay. Get the fundamentals working first.
  - Full-featured multiplayer: Lobby + gameplay sync + coin/hazard sync + level progression + countdown timer + game over sync. Complete end-to-end multiplayer experience.

How should the game handle player deaths in multiplayer?
Options:
  - Independent lives: Each player has their own 3 lives. If you die, you respawn. If you run out of lives, you spectate until the level ends.
  - Shared lives pool: All players share a pool of lives. Any player dying costs the team a life. Game over when the pool is empty.
  - Infinite respawn: Players respawn infinitely — no lives system in multiplayer. Focus is on completing levels together, not survival.
[2026-02-16T23:48:36.398Z] ========== END WORKER QUESTION #1 ==========

