========== WORKER PLAN #1 ==========
[2026-02-16T23:54:18.653Z] {
  "plan": "# Add Co-op Multiplayer to Platform Quest\n\n## Context\n\nPlatform Quest is a Phaser 3 TypeScript platformer with 5 levels. It already has a complete but **unintegrated** PeerJS-based networking layer (`PeerManager` + `MessageTypes` with 15 message types). The goal is to wire up co-op multiplayer for 2-4 players using the existing P2P infrastructure. Scope: lobby system, remote player rendering with position sync, coin sync, and level progression. Each player has independent lives (3 each, spectate when out).\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n### Step 1: Config + Boot textures (trivial)\n\n**`src/config/gameConfig.ts`** - Add helper for indexed player textures:\n```typescript\n// Add to TEXTURES object:\nPLAYER_INDEXED: (index: number) => `player_${index}`,\n```\n\n**`src/scenes/BootScene.ts`** - Generate 4 colored player textures (`player_0` through `player_3`) using `PLAYER_COLORS` from config. Add a `generateColoredPlayers(g)` method looping over colors with matching lighter face tints.\n\n### Step 2: Player entity changes\n\n**`src/entities/Player.ts`** - Three additions:\n1. Accept optional `playerIndex` param (default 0), use `player_${playerIndex}` texture\n2. Add `getNetworkState()` returning `{x, y, velocityX, velocityY, flipX, isDead}`\n3. Add `respawn(x, y)` method (clear tint, reset position/velocity, set isDead=false) -- needed because multiplayer must NOT call `scene.restart()` on death\n\n### Step 3: New RemotePlayer entity\n\n**New file: `src/entities/RemotePlayer.ts`** (~100 lines)\n- Physics sprite with `body.allowGravity = false` (position driven by network, not local physics)\n- `applyPositionUpdate(snapshot)` stores target position from network\n- `update(delta)` lerps sprite toward target at factor 0.3 per frame\n- `showDeath()` / `showRespawn(x,y)` for visual state changes\n- Name tag text above sprite\n- Color based on `playerIndex`\n\n### Step 4: HUD changes\n\n**`src/ui/HUD.ts`** - Expand constructor to accept `isMultiplayer` and `roomCode` params. Add:\n- `showExitCountdown(seconds)` - centered countdown text\n- `showSpectating()` - \"OUT OF LIVES\" overlay\n- Room code display (top-right) in multiplayer mode\n- Store `scene` reference for creating text dynamically\n\n### Step 5: MainMenuScene - mode selection\n\n**`src/scenes/MainMenuScene.ts`** - Replace single \"Press SPACE\" with:\n- `[ SINGLEPLAYER ]` button -> GameScene directly (existing behavior)\n- `[ MULTIPLAYER ]` button -> shows \"Create Room\" / \"Join Room\" sub-options -> LobbyScene\n\n### Step 6: New LobbyScene\n\n**New file: `src/scenes/LobbyScene.ts`** (~200 lines)\n\nAccepts `{ mode: 'create' | 'join' }` from MainMenuScene.\n\n**Create mode (host)**:\n- Call `PeerManager.getInstance().createRoom()`, display room code\n- Add self as Player 1, listen for peer connections\n- On connection: assign playerIndex, broadcast `LOBBY_STATE`\n- Show \"Start Game\" button (enabled when all ready, >= 2 players)\n- On start: broadcast `START_GAME`, transition to GameScene with multiplayer data\n\n**Join mode (client)**:\n- Show room code input (keyboard listener, 6 chars, alphanumeric)\n- Call `peerManager.joinRoom(code)` on submit\n- Listen for `LOBBY_STATE` to display player list\n- \"Ready\" toggle button sends `PLAYER_READY` to host\n- On `START_GAME` received: transition to GameScene\n\n**Scene data passed to GameScene**: `{ level, score, lives, isMultiplayer: true, players: PlayerInfo[], localPlayerIndex }`\n\n### Step 7: GameScene multiplayer integration (biggest change)\n\n**`src/scenes/GameScene.ts`** (~250 lines added)\n\n**New properties**: `isMultiplayer`, `peerManager`, `remotePlayers` map, `allPlayers`, `localPlayerIndex`, `positionTimer`, `allScores`, `allLives`, `collectedCoinIndices` set, `playersAtExit` set, countdown state.\n\n**Key methods**:\n\n| Method | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `setupMultiplayer()` | Create RemotePlayer instances, register handlers, start position timer |\n| `registerNetworkHandlers()` | Wire up handlers for all message types |\n| `broadcastPosition()` | Send POSITION_UPDATE every 50ms |\n| `handleRemoteCoinCollected(index)` | Disable coin sprite by index |\n| `handleRemotePlayerDied/Respawned()` | Update RemotePlayer visuals |\n| `handleRemoteReachExit()` | Track who's at exit |\n| `startExitCountdown()` | Host: 5s countdown, broadcast each second |\n| `advanceLevel()` | Host: broadcast LEVEL_ADVANCE, transition |\n| `checkAllPlayersDead()` | Host: if all lives=0, broadcast GAME_OVER |\n| `cleanupMultiplayer()` | Destroy timers, remote players, clear handlers |\n\n**Critical: Star topology relay** - When host receives any client message, it must relay via `broadcastExcept(fromPeerId, msg)` so other clients see it. Without this, Client B never sees Client C's actions.\n\n**Critical: No scene.restart()** - In multiplayer, deaths use in-place `player.respawn()` instead of restarting the scene (which would destroy remote players and network state).\n\n**Coin collection**
